deck:
Nicols Selma is an Argentinian Artist, born in Buenos Aires; he is currently working with Dark Horse Comics as a penciller in the new series written by Gail Simmons, Tomb Raider. Earlier this year he also had the opportunity to work as a co-owner artist for the same company with Justin Aclin. Together they gave life to the mini-series S.H.O.O.T First. 

He has also had the privilege of being in the animation industry for over 10 years, working in animated productions for Argentina and Mxico.
name: Nicols Daniel Selma

deck: Matt Smigiel is an illustrator living in the New Hampshire area. His work can be seen in various single issues and graphic novels for Boom! Studios, as well as in a myriad of other pieces for a myriad of other clients. He likes jellyfish and watching Seinfeld.
name: Matt Smigiel

deck: Vanessa Beckmann is burgeoning young colourist from Alberta, Canada. She has worked on several short stories in the past, but Paradox is her first big project. She likes video games, dinosaurs, cartoons and comic books.
name: Vanessa Beckmann

deck: Jack McGuigan has had a variety of day jobs, from playhouse salesman to dog walker to billboard designer, but all he really wants to do is make comic books. He lives in Chicago with his wife and dog, and is usually wearing a hat.
name: Jack McGuigan
